(2, 4, 1, 'You Tube', '1_IRqHvDLMnpzXOAcLjpV5nQ_1735206532.png', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our video course materials, combined with lab demonstrations, provide a dynamic and interactive learning experience that caters to both theoretical and practical aspects of the course. The video lectures present core concepts in an engaging, easy-to-follow format, allowing students to absorb key information at their own pace. Accompanying these lectures are hands-on lab demonstrations, which showcase real-world applications and experiments, giving students the opportunity to see theory in action. These lab videos are designed to simulate practical work, allowing students to understand complex processes, techniques, and problem-solving strategies. All video materials, including both lectures and lab demos, are accessible through the learning management system (LMS), and can be viewed on various devices, such as desktops, tablets, or smartphones. This on-demand access allows students to revisit content as needed and study at their convenience, reinforcing their understanding. Additionally, many lab demonstrations come with supplementary resources, step-by-step guides, and interactive exercises to further enhance the learning experience. Whether you&rsquo;re watching a lecture or exploring a lab demo, the combination of visual and practical learning ensures a comprehensive and engaging educational journey.</p>', '[{\"title\":\"Flexure behavior of Simply supported RC Beam - Structural Engineering Lab\",\"YoutubeLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=zG1fpjE6NGg\"},{\"title\":\"Elevation of Building in Remote Elevation Method by Using Total Station - Survey Lab\",\"YoutubeLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=NUewkIwSTCs\"},{\"title\":\"Optimum coagulant Dosage for waste water - Environmental Engineering Lab\",\"YoutubeLink\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=RU-39H6jQrY\"},{\"title\":\"Coefficient of Discharge for Venturimeter - Fluid Mechanics Lab\